<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-016-189 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 451 168</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  Nov 5 1991* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Traveling Software names new sales/marketing VP. (vice-president)(Marco Hegyi)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Mallory, Jim.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Traveling Software Inc. (Officials and employees).andO;Topic:     New AppointmentPromotion of Employee.andO;Person:    Hegyi, Marco (Selection, appointment, resignation, etc.); Scott,Jonathan (Selection, appointment, resignation, etc.).andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Traveling Software Names New Sales/Marketing VP 11/05/91 BOTHELL, WASHINGTON,U.S.A., 1991 NOV 5 (NB) -- Traveling Software has appointed Marco Hegyi itsnew vice-president of sales and marketing.andM;Hegyi replaces Jonathan Scott, who was promoted to chief operating officer(COO) in July of this year.andP;  Hegyi will have responsibility for worldwidesales, marketing and customer service.andM;Speaking of his replacement, Scott said: &quot;Marco has been involved inmanagement in the computer software industry for eight years and brings awealth of experience to Traveling Software.&quot;andM;Prior to joining Traveling Software, Hegyi served as the director ofmarketing for the Information Access division of Software Publishing, inMountain View, California.andP;  Prior to that he was vice- president of marketingand product planning at Microrim in Redmond, Washington.andP;  He was also atAshton-Tate in a marketing position.andP;  He holds a degree in computer sciencefrom the University of California at Irvine.andM;Traveling Software develops products that connect various types of computers,allowing for the transfer of data between different platforms.andP;  They alsomarket products that allow for the uploading and downloading of handheldorganizers and palmtop PCs such as the Casioi B.O.S.S., the HP 95LX and theSharp Wizard.andM;(Jim Mallory/19911105/Press contact: Marci Maule, Traveling Software,206-483-8088)</TEXT></DOC>